architecture-overhaul was deleted after merge.
Only main existed before creating ux-refinement.

Project overview:
- Fantasy overworld hex map web app.
- Leaflet-based map with parchment UI aesthetic.
- Codex acts as an in-world atlas/database browser for:
  - Regions
  - POIs
  - NPCs
  - Hexes
- Heavy emphasis on immersive parchment UI, readable lore presentation, and app-like UX.

Recent completed architecture work:
- Split giant CSS into focused files under /css.
- Split giant app.js into focused JS files under /js.
- Kept scripts as plain global scripts, not ES modules.
- Current JS architecture includes:
  - data-loader.js
  - app-core.js
  - map-ui.js
