Recent confirmed fixes/polish:
- POI/NPC list pages use shared rendering and dynamic field filters.
- Desktop POI/NPC controls cleaned up:
  - no unnecessary “Filter & Sort” heading on desktop
  - no Apply button on desktop
  - filters still apply instantly on change
- Mobile POI/NPC controls still use Filter & Sort popup:
  - popup heading retained
  - Apply button retained
  - inherited compact selector style looks good on mobile
- Filter-field select boxes now visually match the ASC/DESC button:
  - compact button-like style
  - fixed SVG down-arrow
  - no clipping/artifact issue
- Search placeholder changed to:
  “Consult the Codex...”
- Search input text centered.
- Empty search landing helper removed.
- Search result group order changed:
  top row: POIs / NPCs
  bottom row: Hexes / Regions
- Search still shows “No matching ...” messages after typing.
- 95 easter egg still toggles retro Codex icon.
- Retro Codex text readability improved:
  - gold CODEX text retained
  - darker shadow in retro mode
  - subtle dark radial backing behind text only when retro label is visible
- Database loading improved:
  - Google Sheets now load in parallel
  - if Codex opens before db finishes loading, it auto-refreshes when db loads
  - if db fails, Codex shows an error instead of hanging forever
- Desktop smoke test passed.
- Mobile checklist passed.

Known outstanding UX issues / next roadmap:
1. Mobile search UX overhaul is the top priority.
   Current issue:
   - On mobile, only POIs and NPCs are comfortably visible.
   - Hexes and Regions are pushed down.
   - Result group scrollboxes are too small.
   - Need better mobile search layout.
   Possible directions:
   - overall page scroll instead of four trapped scrollboxes
   - collapsible result groups
   - result counts
   - mobile-specific ordering/layout if needed
   - keep desktop search order POIs / NPCs / Hexes / Regions unless there is a better reason to change it

2. Detail page UX refinement:
   - Mobile POI/NPC detail pages may need better real estate usage.
   - Journal/Lore panes may be too shallow on some screens.
   - Consider hybrid overall page scroll plus internal scroll regions, but inspect existing code/CSS first.

3. Region index redesign:
   - More atlas-like archival presentation.
   - Hard A-Z sorting.
   - Future thumbnail support.
   - Possible continent/zone grouping later.

4. Search refinement:
   - exact-match priority
   - relevance weighting
   - match highlighting
   - result counts
   - possible fuzzy matching

5. Hex detail enrichment:
   - richer summaries
   - better relational browsing
   - more “atlas entry” feel

Implementation philosophy:
- Read actual current files before proposing changes.
- Prefer surgical modifications over rewrites.
- Maintain existing architecture.
- Avoid duplicate IDs or duplicate control markup.
- Be careful with desktop/mobile divergence:
  - desktop should remain immersive atlas spread
  - mobile should become more app-like and space-efficient
- We can now use the GitHub connector to read and modify files directly, but changes should still be described clearly.
- Continue committing directly to the working branch only when explicitly permitted.

